guide dogs on ships k so i know guide dogs can go to the mall and museum and stuff like that with blind people but r they allowed to go on ships and cruises with blind people yes they are i work in the port and deal with cruise ships all day i have seen blind people and their dogs take cruises several times the only issue i have heard that has come up before is the one about a place to go for the dog to relieve himself there is no cruise line in the world that i know that wants to be known as not accommodating to the blind or any type of handicap people i bring my dogs on the ships all the time as working dogs Cruise ship Blindness Cruiser USS Missouri (BB-63) Ship Bridgetown USS Forrestal (CVA-59) USS Arkansas (BB-33) USS Whale (SS-239) USS Wasp (CV-18) USS Sea Dog (SS-401) Global Positioning System USS Midway (CV-41) USS Wallace L. Lind (DD-703) Blind Ambition USS Hancock (CV-19) Service dog Unterseeboot 505 USS Ticonderoga (CV-14) Houston, Texas Convoy USS Williamson (DD-244) USS New Jersey (BB-62) SS Andrea Doria Disability USS Topeka (CL-67) USS Chicago (CA-136) USS Salem (CA-139) Tenjiku shogi White Pass and Yukon Route Cruise missile National Library for the Blind Shaggy dog story USS Taussig (DD-746) USS Ault (DD-698) USS Sterlet (SS-392) USS Yorktown (CV-10) German Shepherd Dog USS Tracy (DD-214) USS Truxtun (DLGN-35) Betting (poker) USS Waldron (DD-699) Guide dog USS Harder (SS-257) USS Volador (SS-490) USS Agerholm (DD-826) Second Battle of the Atlantic Glorious First of June USCGC Taney (WHEC-37) Political correctness United States Navy USS Wahoo (SS-565) Joke TSMS Lakonia USS Turner Joy (DD-951) USS Whipple (DD-217) Professional wrestling match types USS Ajax (AR-6) USS Springfield (CL-66) USS Augusta (CA-31) USS Laffey (DD-724) Ernest Shackleton Indian Navy USS Ranger (CVA-61) USS America (CV-66) Dog agility USS Willard Keith (DD-775) USS Allen M. Sumner (DD-692) Working dog NS Savannah USS Wyoming (BB-32) USS Richmond (1860) USS Walker (DD-517) Sevent